def: A thin, loosely woven, twilled worsted stuff.In blue shalloon shall Hannibal be clad. Swift.
To make smaller by a half step; to make (an interval) less thanminor; as, a diminished seventh.
A maker of scholia; a commentator or annotator.No . . . quotations from Talmudists and scholiasts . . . ever marredthe effect of his grave temperate discourses. Macaulay.
A rounded tooth on the edge of a leaf.
A finding of carriages, carts, etc., for the transportation ofgoods, produce, etc. Ainsworth.

A plant of the genus Allium (A. sativum is the cultivatedvariety), having a bulbous root, a very strong smell, and an acrid,pungent taste. Each root is composed of several lesser bulbs, calledcloves of garlic, inclosed in a common membranous coat, and easilyseparable.
